summary: I think Jon bend the knee because he saw 'what she was'. D&D has been building the ground for her fall since s7. Don't trust Jon...
question: I think Jon bend the knee because he saw 'what she was'. D&D has been building the ground for her fall since s7. Don't trust Jon did it because he's in love. And Maisie's dick quote is odd and ominous. lol  D&D portray their romance as one sided. And Jon will choose his family over her. And such way D&D will save his face and portray her in very unflattering lights. It's very interesting to see Dany's behavior when she loses  everything. It's smth we  haven't seen since s1. It'll be entertaining
answer: If Pol Jon is canon then it’ll be subtle and will probably be revealed while Dany is starting to lose it. In S1 she had nothing and when she lost Drogo (if you can lose a rapist) and Rhaego, she gained dragons immediately after. So it genuinely will be interesting to see what happens when she loses her armies, dragons and allies. What will Dany do then? I kind of doubt she’ll just give up, she’s too tenacious.

summary: EMILIA CLARKE “A few weeks after that second surgery, I went with a few other cast members to Comic-Con, in San Diego. The fans...
caption:
EMILIA CLARKE

“A few weeks after that second surgery, I went with a few other cast members to Comic-Con, in San Diego. The fans at Comic-Con are hardcore; you don’t want to disappoint them. There were several thousand people in the audience, and, right before we went on to answer questions, I was hit by a horrific headache. Back came that sickeningly familiar sense of fear. I thought, This is it. My time is up; I’ve cheated death twice and now he’s coming to claim me. As I stepped offstage, my publicist looked at me and asked what was wrong. I told her, but she said that a reporter from MTV was waiting for an interview. I figured, if I’m going to go, it might as well be on live television.” - “A Battle for My Life”

summary: Reading your commentary about projecting help me understand why Sansa always being blamed despite it's Arya faults. It's true...
question: Reading your commentary about projecting help me understand why Sansa always being blamed despite it's Arya faults. It's true Arya is younger. Still she is only 2 year younger. Sansa and Arya still in the same age group. Even back in S1, Arya was the one who provoked, humiliated, and attacked Sansa first. However, Sansa still being blamed and hated for Arya actions, even after Arya want to murder and flay her. Even devil like Roose Bolton refused to murder Ramsay because of kinslayer curse.
answer: I have seen so many Arya-Sansa fanart where Arya as a young child and Sansa in her mid to late teens when they’re in the same age group like you said. Sansa has many passionate fans but we rarely project onto her. We are sympathetic, we want what’s best for Sansa but we don’t see her as this victim of the world from day one. Even the recent Ned critical metas are about examining a dynamic people ignored because they’re too busy vilifying Sansa for everything. Arya stans project their issues onto Arya so hard that they have a version of her that doesn’t exist in either book or show canon. They think everyone bullied Arya, Sansa ruled the castle, Catelyn was abusive towards Arya, Arya only had Jon and her family. The reality is Arya didn’t get along with Sansa, who was good at being a lady but that didn’t give the power people imagine that it did (there is no power imbalance), and Arya had a good relationship with nearly all her siblings and her mother. Because Arya stans are obsessed with Arya being right, they’re incapable of admitting it when she’s wrong. There are entire metas on our side about what Sansa did wrong while asking Northern Houses to join her cause but you’ll never find something like in Arya stan’s blog. I can only think of a handful who thought Arya was being unnecessarily malicious in S7 and even fewer who thought Arya was a bully in S1.
